1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Charles Joseph
3 "CJ" Christ.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on May 20, 2026,
6 of Charles Joseph "CJ" Christ; and
7 WHEREAS, Charles Joseph "CJ" Christ was born in 1929 on a farm in Mowata,
8 Louisiana, and was one of seven children born to Lawrence and Ada Christ; he moved to
9 Lake Charles, Louisiana, with his family during World War II and attended McNeese State
10 University; and
11 WHEREAS, Mr. Christ cherished his siblings, Ruth, Bobby, Francis, Geraldine,
12 Julie, and Jeanette; and
13 WHEREAS, Mr. Christ joined the United States Air Force in 1949 and flew twenty-
14 three combat missions in B-29 bombers over North Korea; after completing his military
15 service, he moved to Houma, Louisiana, and resided there for the remainder of his life; and
16 WHEREAS, during the mid-1950s, Mr. Christ performed impromptu air shows
17 above Houma in his P-51 Mustang fighter aircraft; he married Patricia Wurzlow in 1959 and
18 fathered three children; and
19 WHEREAS, in the 1970s, Mr. Christ operated a successful aviation business, Houma
20 Aviation, at the Houma Airport; in the 2000s, he founded the Regional Military Museum,
