1 which has grown into a publicly-funded, veteran-run institution that receives overwhelming
2 support from citizens of the tri-parish area; and
3 WHEREAS, Mr. Christ was a well-respected author and historian who studied the
4 history of the United States Gulf during World War II; he was also an avid aviator, mariner,
5 and scuba diver; he traveled the world and touched the lives of all who met him with his
6 infectious sense of humor and passion for adventure; and
7 WHEREAS, Charles Joseph "CJ" Christ is survived by his children, Cheryl (Steve),
8 Bobby (Karen), and Linda; stepson, Jack (Ida); and host of grandchildren and extended
9 family members; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy of his adventurous spirit and
10 passion for life shall live on in perpetuity in the hearts and minds of those who were
11 privileged enough to have known and loved him.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
13 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Charles
14 Joseph "CJ" Christ and does hereby extend sincere wishes that his family, friends, and loved
15 ones find comfort in their shared memories of his beautiful life.
